    "EDENIZED": "Admitted to a state of paradisaic happiness. [R.] Davies (Wit'sPilgr. ).",
    "EDENTAL": "See Edentate, a.-- n. (Zoöl.)",
    "EDENTALOUS": "See Edentate, a.",
    "EDENTATA": "An order of mammals including the armadillos, sloths, andanteaters; -- called also Bruta. The incisor teeth are rarelydeveloped, and in some groups all the teeth are lacking.",
