    "EVOLUTE": "A curve from which another curve, called the involute orevolvent, is described by the end of a thread gradually wound uponthe former, or unwound from it. See Involute. It is the locus of thecenters of all the circles which are osculatory to the given curve orevolvent.",
    "EVOLUTILITY": "The faculty possessed by all substances capable of self-nourishment of manifesting the nutritive acts by changes of form, ofvolume, or of structure. Syd. Soc. Lex.",
    "EVOLUTION": "The formation of an involute by unwrapping a thread from acurve as an evolute. Hutton.",
    "EVOLUTIONAL": "Relating to evolution. \"Evolutional changes.\" H. Spenser.",
