    "EXALT": "To render pure or refined; to intensify or concentrate; as, toexalt the juices of bodies.With chemic art exalts the mineral powers. Pope.",
    "EXALTATE": "Exercising its highest influence; -- said of a planet. [Obs.]Chaucer.",
