    "EXALTED": "Raised to lofty height; elevated; extolled; refined; dignified;sublime.Wiser far than Solomon, Of more exalted mind. Milton.Time never fails to bring every exalted reputation to a strictscrutiny. Ames.-- Ex*alt\"ed*ly, adv.-- Ex*alt\"ed*ness, n. \"The exaltedness of some minds.\" T. Gray.",
