    "EXAMPLE": "To set an example for; to give a precedent for; to exemplify;to give an instance of; to instance. [Obs.] \"I may example mydigression by some mighty precedent.\" Shak.Burke devoted himself to this duty with a fervid assiduity that hasnot often been exampled, and has never been surpassed. J. Morley.",
