    "EXICCATE": "See Exsiccate. [Obs.] Holland.",
    "EXICCATION": "See Exsiccation. [Obs.]",
    "EXIGENCE": "Exigency. Hooker.",
    "EXIGENCY": "The state of being exigent; urgent or exacting want; pressingnecessity or distress; need; a case demanding immediate action,supply, or remedy; as, an unforeseen exigency. \"The present exigencyof his affairs.\" Ludlow.",
    "EXIGENDARY": "See Exigenter.",
