    "EXIGUITY": "Scantiness; smallness; thinness. [R.] Boyle.",
    "EXIGUOUS": "Scanty; small; slender; diminutive. [R.] \"Exiguous resources.\"Carlyle.-- Ex*ig\"uous*ness, n. [R.]",
    "EXILE": "To banish or expel from one's own country or home; to driveaway. \"Exiled from eternal God.\" Tennyson.Calling home our exiled friends abroad. Shak.",
