    "EXINANITION": "n. [L. exinanitio.] An emptying; an enfeebling; exhaustion;humiliation. [Obs.]Fastings to the exinanition of spirits. Jer. Taylor.",
    "EXISTENCY": "Existence. [R.] Sir M. Hale.",
    "EXISTENT": "Having being or existence; existing; being; occurring now;taking place.The eyes and mind are fastened on objects which have no real being,as if they were truly existent. Dryden.",
    "EXISTENTIAL": "Having existence. [Archaic] Bp. Barlow. --Ex`is*ten\"tial*ly,adv. [Archaic]Existentially as well as essentially intelligent. Colerige.",
