    "EXPECTATIVE": "Constituting an object of expectation; contingent. Expectativegrace, a mandate given by the pope or a prince appointing a successorto any benefice before it becomes vacant. Foxe.",
    "EXPECTEDLY": "In conformity with expectation. [R.] Walpole.",
